column3:
+1 @sipa suggestion, something like
```cpp
CTxDestination DecodeDestination(const std::string& str, std::string& error);
CTxDestination DecodeDestination(const std::string& str)
{
    const std::string& error;
    return DecodeDestination(str, error);
}
```
And maybe also embed the error index in the message for now.

Instead of this function, it may be worth just using [`std::iota`](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/algorithm/iota).

The function is equivalent to:

```c++
void push_range(int from, int to, std::vector<int>& vec)
{
    vec.resize(to - from);
    std::iota(vec.begin(), vec.end(), from);
}
```

But I suggest just doing that directly in the call sites.
